label.value: L-ascorbate peroxidase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  L-ascorbate + hydrogen peroxide -eq- dehydroascorbate + 2 H2O.

label.value: manganese peroxidase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  2 Mn2+ + 2 H+ + hydrogen peroxide -eq- 2 Mn3+ + 2 H2O.

label.value: diarylpropane peroxidase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  (3,4-dimethoxyphenyl)methanol + H2O2 -eq- 3,4-dimethoxybenzaldehyde + 2 H2O.

label.value: chloride peroxidase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  2 R-H + 2 chloride + hydrogen peroxide -eq- 2 R-Cl + 2 H2O.

label.value: NADH peroxidase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  H(2)O(2) + H(+) + NADH -eq- 2 H(2)O + NAD(+).

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on hydrogen as donor

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen acts as an electron donor.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on hydrogen as donor, NAD or NADP as acceptor

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen acts as an electron donor and reduces NAD or NADP.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on hydrogen as donor, cytochrome as acceptor

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen acts as an electron donor and reduces a cytochrome.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on hydrogen as donor, iron-sulfur protein as acceptor

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen acts as an electron donor and reduces an iron-sulfur protein.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on single donors with incorporation of molecular oxygen

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen or electrons are transferred from one donor, and molecular oxygen is incorporated into a donor.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on single donors with incorporation of molecular oxygen, incorporation of two atoms of oxygen

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen or electrons are transferred from one donor, and two oxygen atoms is incorporated into a donor.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on single donors with incorporation of molecular oxygen, incorporation of one atom of oxygen (internal monooxygenases or internal mixed function oxidases)

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen or electrons are transferred from one donor, and one oxygen atom is incorporated into a donor.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen or electrons are transferred from each of two donors, and molecular oxygen is reduced or incorporated into a donor.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen, 2-oxoglutarate as one donor, and incorporation of one atom each of oxygen into both donors

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  A + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 -eq- B + succinate + CO2. This is an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen or electrons are transferred from 2-oxoglutarate and one other donor, and one atom of oxygen is incorporated into each donor.

label.value: gibberellin 3-beta-dioxygenase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  a gibberellin + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 -eq- a 3-beta-hydroxy-gibberellin + succinate + CO2.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen, NAD(P)H as one donor, and incorporation of two atoms of oxygen into one donor

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen or electrons are transferred from NADH or NADPH and one other donor, and two atoms of oxygen are incorporated into one donor.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen, NAD(P)H as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen or electrons are transferred from NADH or NADPH and one other donor, and one atom of oxygen is incorporated into one donor.

label.value: trans-cinnamate 4-monooxygenase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  trans-cinnamate + NADPH + H+ + O2 -eq- 4-hydroxycinnamate + NADP+ + H2O.

label.value: flavonoid 3'-monooxygenase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  a flavonoid + NADPH + H+ + O2 -eq- 3'-hydroxyflavonoid + NADP+ + H2O.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen, reduced flavin or flavoprotein as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen or electrons are transferred from reduced flavin or flavoprotein and one other donor, and one atom of oxygen is incorporated into one donor.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen, reduced iron-sulfur protein as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen or electrons are transferred from reduced iron-sulfur protein and one other donor, and one atom of oxygen is incorporated into one donor.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen, reduced pteridine as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen or electrons are transferred from reduced pteridine and one other donor, and one atom of oxygen is incorporated into one donor.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen, reduced ascorbate as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen or electrons are transferred from reduced ascorbate and one other donor, and one atom of oxygen is incorporated into one donor.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen, another compound as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen or electrons are transferred from each of two donors, and one atom of oxygen is incorporated into one donor.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with oxidation of a pair of donors resulting in the reduction of molecular oxygen to two molecules of water

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen or electrons are transferred from each of two donors, and molecular oxygen is reduced to two molecules of water.

label.value: carotene 7,8-desaturase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  neurosporene + donor-H2 + O2 -eq- lycopene + acceptor + 2 H2O.

label.value: delta12-fatty acid dehydrogenase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  AH(2) + linoleate + O(2) -eq- A + crepenynate + 2 H(2)O.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on superoxide radicals as acceptor

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a superoxide radical (O2- or O2.-) acts as a hydrogen or electron acceptor.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, oxidizing metal ions

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction in which the oxidation state of metal ion is altered.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, oxidizing metal ions, NAD or NADP as acceptor

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction in which the oxidation state of metal ion is altered and NAD+ or NADP+ acts as an electron acceptor.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, oxidizing metal ions, oxygen as acceptor

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction in which the oxidation state of metal ion is altered and oxygen acts as an electron acceptor.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on CH or CH2 groups

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a CH2 group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a hydrogen or electron acceptor.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on CH or CH2 groups, NAD or NADP as acceptor

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a CH2 group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces NAD+ or NADP.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on CH or CH2 groups, oxygen as acceptor

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a CH2 group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces an oxygen molecule.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on CH or CH2 groups, disulfide as acceptor

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a CH2 group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a disulfide group.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on iron-sulfur proteins as donors

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which an iron-sulfur protein acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a hydrogen or electron acceptor.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on iron-sulfur proteins as donors, NAD or NADP as acceptor

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which an iron-sulfur protein acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces NAD or NADP.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on iron-sulfur proteins as donors, dinitrogen as acceptor

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which an iron-sulfur protein acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces dinitrogen.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on reduced flavodoxin as donor

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which reduced flavodoxin acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a hydrogen or electron acceptor.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on reduced flavodoxin as donor, dinitrogen as acceptor

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which reduced flavodoxin acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces dinitrogen.

label.value: transferase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a group, e.g. a methyl group, glycosyl group, acyl group, phosphorus-containing, or other groups, from one compound (generally regarded as the donor) to another compound (generally regarded as the acceptor). Transferase is the systematic name for any enzyme of EC class 2.

label.value: transferase activity, transferring one-carbon groups

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a one-carbon group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

label.value: hydroxymethyl-, formyl- and related transferase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a hydroxymethyl- or formyl group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

label.value: carboxyl- or carbamoyltransferase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a carboxyl- or carbamoyl group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

label.value: transferase activity, transferring aldehyde or ketonic groups

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of an aldehyde or ketonic group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

label.value: transferase activity, transferring acyl groups

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of an acyl group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

label.value: transferase activity, transferring acyl groups other than amino-acyl groups

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of an acyl group, other than amino-acyl, from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

label.value: succinyltransferase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a succinyl (3-carboxypropanoyl) group to an acceptor molecule.

label.value: N-succinyltransferase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a succinyl group to a nitrogen atom on the acceptor molecule.

label.value: O-succinyltransferase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a succinyl group to an oxygen atom on the acceptor molecule.
